x4freetext: The 7 MV CN Van de Graaff accelerator
at the University of Kentucky Accelerator Laboratory
(UKAL).
A 48.6641 g metallic five-
piece sample, isotopically enriched to 99.47(1)%,
was tightly wrapped with plastic to approximately
cylindrical shape with a diameter of 2.05 cm and
height of 3.80 cm.
A Compton-suppressed n-type HPGe detector
with 53% relative efficiency and an energy resolution
of ~2.1 keV FWHM at 1.33 MeV was used. A bismuth
germanate (BGO) annular detector surrounding the main
detector was used for Compton suppression and as an
active shield.

x4freetext: n-gamma, gamma-gamma-coincidences. gamma-ray
excitation functions, angular distributions, and
Doppler shifts were measured with a singles gamma-ray
detector configuration. These yields were measured at
90 degrees.
All uncertainties on gamma-ray yields are
statistical.

x4freetext: For the angular distributions the sample center was
located 8.5(1) cm from the center of the gas cell,
while the detector face was 115(1) cm from the center
of pivot, which was also the sample center.
No information on uncertainties.
These angular distributions were fit to even-order
Legendre polynomial expansions and compared to
calculations from the statistical model code CINDY to
extract level spins and multipolemixing ratios.
